# Automatic redshift service with timer

This will (re)apply redshift on a timer. This is usefull, when disconnecting a display or sleeping the computer resets the screen color.

Link redshift.service and redshift.timer to: `~/.config/systemd/user`

Run once:
systemctl --user daemon-reload
systemctl --user enable redshift.timer
systemctl --user enable resdhift.service
systemctl --user start redshift.timer

NOTE: Disabling a serice `systemctl --user disable redshift.[service,timer] will remove the links from ~/.config/systemd/user`. If you do that, re-link them.
